# Sample lightning transactions using package RBF

This document contains sample fee-bumping scenarios used by lightning nodes to replace a malicious commitment transaction.
Commitments transactions in these test cases don't pay any fees.
The fee-bumping child (the anchor transaction) spends from one or more commitment transactions and an unrelated wallet transaction (used to add funds).

## Basic commitment RBF

The mempool initially contains:

```mempool
 +-----------+  +-----------+
 | CommitTxA |  | ChangeTxA |
 +-----------+  +-----------+
       |              |
       +-----+  +-----+
             |  |
             v  v
         +-----------+
         | AnchorTxA |
         +-----------+
```

## Replace long descendant chain

The mempool initially contains a commitment with a long chain of descendants.
All intermediate descendants are large transactions with a low feerate, but the last descendant is a small transaction with a high feerate.

```mempool
 +-----------+  +-----------+
 | CommitTxA |  | ChangeTxA |
 +-----------+  +-----------+
       |              |
       +-----+  +-----+
             |  |
             v  v
         +-----------+
         | AnchorTxA |
         +-----------+
               |
              ... low feerate descendants
               |
               v
         +------------+
         |  JunkTxAN  | high feerate descendant
         +------------+
```
